<P>HAving already &s;hewed you what Con&s;cience is, and a|bout what it is imployed, and how it is imployed, and given you &s;everal rea|&s;ons why we &s;hould make it our great care &s;o to live, that Con&s;cience may not reproach us while we live, and having made &s;ome U&s;e of the Doctrine, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> now come to re&s;olve two que&s;tions or ca&s;es.</P>
<P N="1">1. The fir&s;t is, how may we &s;o live, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">k and act, and carry our &s;elves, hat Con&s;cience may have no cau&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> to re|pro<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ch <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">s another day?</P>
<P N="2">2. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e have &s;o lived, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o wa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">cted, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;o carried our &s;elves, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">
